  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The normal saline is used in medicine as an intravenous isotonic infusion and for cleaning
      wounds. It is a mild but effective cleaning agent and will not harm normal tissue, unlike
      many stronger antiseptics. It is available and inexpensive in comparison to povidone iodine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
